The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 September is 3,293 (381.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 September, there were 107 new confirmed cases (12.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 September, there were 168 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 36% (61 fewer cases).
